<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-182-880  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 182 880.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Graphics World  April 1989 v12 n4 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Top-down design control. (Pro-assembly module with parametriccapability) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pfitzer, Gary; Robertson, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Parametric Technology Corp introduces Pro-Assembly, a module to beintegrated with the existing parametric solid modeling system,Pro-Engineer.andP;  Pro-Assembly replaces Pro-Layout, the previousassembly module.andP;  Basic to Pro-Assembly is its parametriccapability.andP;  Global relationships are incorporated into thelayout.andP;  As a result, the designer's original intent is preservedwhen parts are added to the design.andP;  Any design can be reduced togeneric parts so that the designer can interchange differentvariations without rebuilding the basic assembly.andP;  Users watchgeometric changes as new values are introduced.andP;  Other productsare similar, according to Haworth Inc director of advancedengineering James Bluhm, but require much more programming.andO;Pro-Assembly costs $2500 when added to Pro-Engineer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Parametric Technology Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Pro-Assembly (Computer graphics software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionComputer GraphicsParametersComputer-Aided DesignModularitySoftware PackagesSolids Modeling.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>